If the `&quot;foo&quot;` was only allocated once, and then reused, the result would be `[&quot;foobar&quot;, &quot;foobar&quot;]` instead, which would violate the [principle of least astonishment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Principle_of_least_astonishment). If someone really wants to do that, the same object should explicitly be used:

